# GrokInstall — Repos to create on GitHub

This document is the exact paste-able content for creating the five new repos that the Master Plan + v1.1 Addendum calls for. Three are needed for upcoming sessions (vscode-grok-yaml, grok-install-action, grok-agents-marketplace); two come from Session 2 of the addendum (grok-repo-chatbot, grok-repo-bot-widget) and are included here so you can create them in one batch.

For each repo:

- **GitHub description** (350 char max) — paste into the description field at creation
- **Topics** (max 20) — paste under repo Settings → Topics
- **Initial visibility** — Public for all (it's an open ecosystem)
- **License** — MIT
- **Add a README** — leave **unchecked** at creation (Session 1's premium README sweep will create it)
- **Add .gitignore** — leave unchecked (will be added per repo's stack)
- **Default branch** — `main`
- **Social preview image** — set after Session 1 generates the banner (use the generated SVG converted to 1280×640 PNG)

Once created, each repo will get its premium README, hero banner, and `/docs/index.html` hub during Session 3 of the addendum (the sweep session).

---

